verses.verse: O be ioyfull in God (all ye lodes) serue the LORDE wt gladnes, come before his presence wt ioye.
Be ye sure, yt the LORDE he is God:
It is he yt hath made vs, & not we oure selues: we are but his people, & the shepe of his pasture.
go youre waye in to his gates the with thankesgeuynge, & in to his courtes wt prayse: be thakfull vnto him, & speake good of his name.
For the LORDE is gracious, his mercy is euerlastinge, and his treuth endureth from generacion to generacion.
